Posted: Thu Apr 09, 2009 7:00 am
That is always what I have considered the ultimate chokepoint for Facebook, MySpace and Twitter: you never know who is going to be reading.If you are going to be completely candid, you'll have to write under a pseudonym. The problem with that is that no one you know will find you -- you have to tell them that you are "CoolDude4567." All of these great stories of long lost friends finding each other will never happen.If you do write under your real name, the specter of self-censorship will ruin it. If you assume that everything you post will be read by your boss, your family, the police, your coworkers, etc., etc., you are probably going to end up making bland comments about the weather. How boring.I'm not on any of those social networking sites for that reason. This story only strengthens my aversion to them.
