quote:Originally posted by Dragonscript:Freedom of speech baby, its a dual edged sword. I'll second that; In fact I don't think we take it far enough, because the *real* crazy people often aren't run out of town (think Jack Thompson, or Bill Donohue, or Ray Comfort, or Ted Haggart). Let people say whatever insane things they want, but hold them accountable for it (preferably not years after the fact).However, the death threats and gunshot to the house in this case are abhorrent; bogus vigilante justice is not the way to do it.I'll also agree with the other folks that the principal's act of taking the web-rant and republishing it in another format (as a letter to the editor in the paper) does seem to be against how most copyright gets treated. Last I knew, artists/writers got a say in where their work gets published. But I haven't read the article, so maybe the newspaper actually picked quotes and added commentary. That's transformative and fair use as I see it.
